title: Work-family balance can tip wrong way for some young doctors

title_detail.value: Work-family balance can tip wrong way for some young doctors

summary: Female medical interns are more likely to suffer from symptoms of depression than their male counterparts, and the conflict between work and family responsibilities is a factor in that gender difference about a third of the time, suggests research.
